text: Didier Kiki (born November 30, 1995) is a Beninese sprinter. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the men's 200 metres race; his time of 22.27 seconds in the heats did not qualify him for the semifinals. ==References== Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Beninese male sprinters Category:Olympic athletes of Benin Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics
